        <h1 class="heading-large">Roadmap</h1>
            <p>Here’s a list of the new functionality we’re planning to offer through GOV.UK&nbsp;Pay.</p>

            <p class="panel panel-border-wide">This roadmap is a only a guide and may change from month to month.</p>

            <h2 class="heading-small">July-September 2017</h2>
              <ul class="list list-bullet">
                <li>Improved onboarding experience</li>
                <li>Self service account creation and team management (DONE)</li>
                <li>Support for Barclays ePDQ payment gateway (DONE)</li>
                <li>Improved refund-related reporting</li>
                <li>Test and increase performance (transactions per second)</li>
                <li>Improved how we deploy applications in our infrastructure</li>
              </ul>
      
      <h2 class="heading-small">October-December 2017</h2>
              <ul class="list list-bullet">
                <li>Improved settlement reporting for bank reconciliation</li>
                <li>3D Secure for Barclays Smartpay and ePDQ</li>
                <li>Automated contract and infrastructure testing</li>
                <li>Enable services to take ad hoc payments online</li>
              </ul>
      
            <h2 class="heading-small">January-March 2018</h2>
              <ul class="list list-bullet">
                <li>Reporting across multiple services</li>
                <li>Improving reporting for high volume services</li>
                <li>Improved disaster recovery</li>
                <li>Make it possible for end users to pay invoices online</li>
              </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-small">Later</h2>
              <ul class="list list-bullet">
                <li>Support for Direct Debit</li>
                <li>Foreign currency and language support</li>
                <li>Telephone card payments</li>
                <li>Support for eWallets</li>
                <li>Support for Pay via Bank Account (PSD2)</li>
                <li>Enable services to publish and sell from a product catalogue</li>
              </ul>

            <h2 class="heading-medium">Queries and suggestions</h2>
            <p>If you want to find out more about these features, or have some needs that GOV.UK Pay isn’t yet meeting, please get in touch with us by emailing <a href="mailto:govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk">govuk-pay-support@digital.cabinet-office.gov.uk</a> or chat with us in our <a href="https://ukgovernmentdigital.slack.com/messages/govuk-pay">cross-government Slack channel</a>.</p>
